# API & WebSocket Contract

- **Message types**: Client sends `speech-start`, `speech-end`, `interview-start`, `interview-end` + binary PCM. Server sends `status`, `transcript`, `ai-response`, `tts-audio` (then binary), `error`, `profiler-stats`. Do not rename or drop fields used by the other side.
- **Error codes**: Use existing codes only—`PROVIDERS_NOT_READY`, `STT_ERROR`, `BUFFER_ERROR`, `INVALID_JSON`, `SERVER_ERROR`. Add new codes only when adding new failure modes; document in `docs/` or SKILL.
- **CamelCase**: Backend schemas use `model_dump(by_alias=True)`; frontend expects camelCase (`isFinal`, `isComplete`, `focusAreas`). Keep `backend/models/schemas.py` and `frontend/.../websocket.models.ts` aligned.
